results.name: hotosm_npl_roads
results.notes:
OpenStreetMap contains roughly 280.7 million km of roads in this region. Based on AI-mapped estimates, this is approximately 84 % of the total road length in the dataset region. The average age of data for the region is 3 years  ( Last edited 5 months ago ) and 7% of roads were added or updated in the last 6 months.
Read about what this summary means : [indicators](https://github.com/hotosm/raw-data-api/tree/develop/docs/src/stats/indicators.md) , [metrics](https://github.com/hotosm/raw-data-api/tree/develop/docs/src/stats/metrics.md)


This theme includes all OpenStreetMap features in this area matching ( Learn what tags means [here](https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Tags) ) :

tags['highway'] IS NOT NULL

results.notes:
This theme includes all OpenStreetMap features in this area matching ( Learn what tags means [here](https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Tags) ) :

tags['waterway'] IS NOT NULL OR tags['water'] IS NOT NULL OR tags['natural'] IN ('water','wetland','bay')

Features may have these attributes:

- [name](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:name)
- [name:en](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:name:en)
- [waterway](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:waterway)
- [covered](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:covered)
- [width](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:width)
- [depth](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:depth)
- [layer](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:layer)
- [blockage](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:blockage)
- [tunnel](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:tunnel)
- [natural](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:natural)
- [water](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:water)
- [source](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:source)
- [name:ne](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:name:ne)

This dataset is one of many [OpenStreetMap exports on
HDX](https://data.humdata.org/organization/hot).
See the [Humanitarian OpenStreetMap Team](http://hotosm.org/) website for more
information.

organization.description:
**For up-to-the-minute exports from OpenStreetMap in a variety of formats for GPS and GIS, visit http://export.hotosm.org**

Humanitarian OpenStreetMap Team (HOT) acts as a bridge between the traditional humanitarian responders and the OpenStreetMap Community. HOT works both remotely and physically in countries to assist the collection of geographic data, usage of that information and training others in OpenStreetMap.

results.notes:
This theme includes all OpenStreetMap features in this area matching ( Learn what tags means [here](https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Tags) ) :

tags['amenity'] IS NOT NULL OR tags['man_made'] IS NOT NULL OR tags['shop'] IS NOT NULL OR tags['tourism'] IS NOT NULL

Features may have these attributes:

- [name](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:name)
- [name:en](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:name:en)
- [amenity](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:amenity)
- [man_made](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:man_made)
- [shop](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:shop)
- [tourism](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:tourism)
- [opening_hours](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:opening_hours)
- [beds](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:beds)
- [rooms](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:rooms)
- [addr:full](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:addr:full)
- [addr:housenumber](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:addr:housenumber)
- [addr:street](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:addr:street)
- [addr:city](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:addr:city)
- [source](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:source)
- [name:ne](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:name:ne)

This dataset is one of many [OpenStreetMap exports on
HDX](https://data.humdata.org/organization/hot).
See the [Humanitarian OpenStreetMap Team](http://hotosm.org/) website for more
information.

organization.description:
**For up-to-the-minute exports from OpenStreetMap in a variety of formats for GPS and GIS, visit http://export.hotosm.org**

Humanitarian OpenStreetMap Team (HOT) acts as a bridge between the traditional humanitarian responders and the OpenStreetMap Community. HOT works both remotely and physically in countries to assist the collection of geographic data, usage of that information and training others in OpenStreetMap.

results.notes:
This theme includes all OpenStreetMap features in this area matching ( Learn what tags means [here](https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Tags) ) :

tags['aeroway'] IS NOT NULL OR tags['building'] = 'aerodrome' OR tags['emergency:helipad'] IS NOT NULL OR tags['emergency'] = 'landing_site'

Features may have these attributes:

- [name](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:name)
- [name:en](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:name:en)
- [aeroway](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:aeroway)
- [building](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:building)
- [emergency](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:emergency)
- [emergency:helipad](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:emergency:helipad)
- [operator:type](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:operator:type)
- [capacity:persons](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:capacity:persons)
- [addr:full](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:addr:full)
- [addr:city](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:addr:city)
- [source](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:source)
- [name:ne](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:name:ne)

This dataset is one of many [OpenStreetMap exports on
HDX](https://data.humdata.org/organization/hot).
See the [Humanitarian OpenStreetMap Team](http://hotosm.org/) website for more
information.

organization.description:
**For up-to-the-minute exports from OpenStreetMap in a variety of formats for GPS and GIS, visit http://export.hotosm.org**

Humanitarian OpenStreetMap Team (HOT) acts as a bridge between the traditional humanitarian responders and the OpenStreetMap Community. HOT works both remotely and physically in countries to assist the collection of geographic data, usage of that information and training others in OpenStreetMap.

results.name: hotosm_npl_education_facilities
results.notes:
This theme includes all OpenStreetMap features in this area matching ( Learn what tags means [here](https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Tags) ) :

tags['amenity'] IN ('kindergarten', 'school', 'college', 'university') OR tags['building'] IN ('kindergarten', 'school', 'college', 'university')

Features may have these attributes:

- [name](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:name)
- [name:en](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:name:en)
- [amenity](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:amenity)
- [building](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:building)
- [operator:type](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:operator:type)
- [capacity:persons](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:capacity:persons)
- [addr:full](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:addr:full)
- [addr:city](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:addr:city)
- [source](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:source)
- [name:ne](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:name:ne)

This dataset is one of many [OpenStreetMap exports on
HDX](https://data.humdata.org/organization/hot).
See the [Humanitarian OpenStreetMap Team](http://hotosm.org/) website for more
information.

organization.title: Humanitarian OpenStreetMap Team (HOT)
organization.description:
**For up-to-the-minute exports from OpenStreetMap in a variety of formats for GPS and GIS, visit http://export.hotosm.org**

Humanitarian OpenStreetMap Team (HOT) acts as a bridge between the traditional humanitarian responders and the OpenStreetMap Community. HOT works both remotely and physically in countries to assist the collection of geographic data, usage of that information and training others in OpenStreetMap.

results.name: hotosm_npl_health_facilities
results.notes:
This theme includes all OpenStreetMap features in this area matching ( Learn what tags means [here](https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Tags) ) :

tags['healthcare'] IS NOT NULL OR tags['amenity'] IN ('doctors', 'dentist', 'clinic', 'hospital', 'pharmacy')

Features may have these attributes:

- [name](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:name)
- [name:en](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:name:en)
- [amenity](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:amenity)
- [building](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:building)
- [healthcare](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:healthcare)
- [healthcare:speciality](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:healthcare:speciality)
- [operator:type](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:operator:type)
- [capacity:persons](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:capacity:persons)
- [addr:full](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:addr:full)
- [addr:city](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:addr:city)
- [source](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:source)
- [name:ne](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:name:ne)

This dataset is one of many [OpenStreetMap exports on
HDX](https://data.humdata.org/organization/hot).
See the [Humanitarian OpenStreetMap Team](http://hotosm.org/) website for more
information.

organization.title: Humanitarian OpenStreetMap Team (HOT)
organization.description:
**For up-to-the-minute exports from OpenStreetMap in a variety of formats for GPS and GIS, visit http://export.hotosm.org**

Humanitarian OpenStreetMap Team (HOT) acts as a bridge between the traditional humanitarian responders and the OpenStreetMap Community. HOT works both remotely and physically in countries to assist the collection of geographic data, usage of that information and training others in OpenStreetMap.

tags['railway'] IN ('rail','station')

Features may have these attributes:

- [name](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:name)
- [name:en](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:name:en)
- [railway](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:railway)
- [ele](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:ele)

- [addr:full](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:addr:full)
- [addr:city](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:addr:city)
- [source](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:source)
- [name:ne](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:name:ne)

HDX](https://data.humdata.org/organization/hot).

information.

Humanitarian OpenStreetMap Team (HOT) acts as a bridge between the traditional humanitarian responders and the OpenStreetMap Community. HOT works both remotely and physically in countries to assist the collection of geographic data, usage of that information and training others in OpenStreetMap.
